1 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
2 Sec. 1. RECREATIONAL TRAILS COMPENSATION STUDY
3 COMMITTEE; REPORT
4 (a) Creation. There is created the Recreational Trails Compensation Study
5 Committee to review whether real property owners who allow use of their
6 property for public recreational trails should receive compensation or other
7 benefit.
8 (b) Membership.
9 (1) The Recreational Trails Compensation Study Committee shall be
10 composed of the following members:
11 (A) the Commissioner of Forests, Parks and Recreation or designee;
12 (B) the Commissioner of Taxes or designees;
13 (C) a representative of the Vermont Trails and Greenways Council,
14 appointed by the Governor;
15 (D) a representative of the Vermont Outdoor Recreation Economic
16 Collaborative, appointed by the Speaker of the House;
17 (E) a representative of a land conservation organization, appointed by
18 the Committee on Committees;
19 (F) a private landowner who has a conservation easement that
20 includes recreation, appointed by the Governor;
