1 (3) A majority of the membership shall constitute a quorum.
2 (4) The Committee shall cease to exist on March 1, 2027.
3 (g) Compensation and reimbursement. Members of the Committee shall be
4 entitled to per diem compensation and reimbursement of expenses as permitted
5 under 32 V.S.A. ยง 1010 for not more than six meetings. These payments shall
6 be made from monies appropriated to the Agency of Natural Resources.
7 (h) Appropriation for Committee consulting. In addition to other funds
8 appropriated to the Department of Forests, Parks and Recreation in fiscal year
9 2026, the sum of $250,000.00 is appropriated to the Department from the
10 General Fund in fiscal year 2026 to:
11 (1) contract with one or more consultants to assist with the required
12 evaluation of the economic impact of the outdoor recreation industry on the
13 economy of Vermont; and
14 (2) support the powers and duties of the Study Committee on
15 development of the report required under this section.
16 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
17 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
